MALE TERMINALIA. Cerci long, pointed at apex, dark brown in colour, clothed in setae. Styli short, rounded and not visible from above. Subgenital plate short, broadly oval, with median indentation (
Fig. 9D
). Last tergite with a distinctive protuberance, resembling a tail stump, that gives this species its name. Folds at base of cerci also pointed on interior edge, giving terminalia shape of a trident when seen from above (
Fig. 9E
).
